Fastest growing e-commerce players ğŸ‘‡

Carvana $CVNA
Vertically integrated auto marketplace with logistics and financing moat; scaling profitably faster than peers. NTM growth ~33.5%.

MercadoLibre $MELI

Sea Limited $SE
Shopee gains share via logistics and ads monetization; improving profitability across ecosystem. NTM growth ~27.4%.

Jumia $JMIA
Localized logistics and payments advantage in Africa; early-stage but improving unit economics. NTM growth ~27.2%.

Shopify $SHOP
Horizontal commerce infrastructure powering merchants globally; strong payments and AI-driven checkout moat. NTM growth ~25.6%.

Global-e $GLBE
Critical infrastructure for cross-border DTC; regulatory complexity strengthens switching costs. NTM growth ~24.2%.

Meta $META
Dominant digital ads platform enabling commerce discovery; monetization strength exceeds direct retail exposure. NTM growth ~19.1%.

Coupang $CPNG
Logistics-led moat in Korea with rising margins; international expansion remains investment-heavy. NTM growth ~15.7%.

Pinterest $PINS
High-intent visual discovery platform monetizing commerce ads without owning transactions. NTM growth ~14.3%.

Amazon $AMZN
Global e-commerce and logistics leader; scale unmatched but growth moderated by size and CapEx intensity. NTM growth ~11.7%.

Instacart $CART
Leader in online grocery and retail media; enterprise tooling offsets maturing consumer growth. NTM growth ~9.7%.

Alibaba Group $BABA
China e-commerce and cloud incumbent; growth constrained by reinvestment cycle and macro pressure. NTM growth ~7.6%.
